think%2C%20as%20the%20US%20dollar%20continues%20to%20come%20under%20pressure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20typically%20stable%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fcurrencies%2Fusd-twd%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETaiwan%20dollar%3C%2Fa%3E%20surged%20by%20as%20much%20as%2010%25%20against%20the%20greenback%20in%20the%20first%20few%20days%20of%20this%20month.%20The%20currency%20is%20now%20about%208%25%20higher%20against%20the%20dollar%20this%20year%20to%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20Asian%20currencies%2C%20including%20those%20from%20Singapore%2C%20South%20Korea%2C%20Malaysia%2C%20China%2C%20and%20Hong%20Kong%2C%20have%20also%20rallied%20over%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20gains%20come%20as%20Asian%20companies%2C%20including%20insurers%20and%20exporters%2C%20move%20money%20out%20of%20US%20assets%20and%20back%20home%20%E2%80%94%20a%20shift%20driven%20in%20part%20by%20the%20weakening%20dollar.%20Many%20didn't%20hedge%20against%20currency%20swings%2C%20so%20they're%20now%20losing%20money%20as%20the%20greenback%20falls%20amid%20fears%20over%20Trump's%20tariffs%20and%20a%20slowing%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrancesco%20Pesole%2C%20an%20ING%20strategist%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20note%20on%20Tuesday%20that%20economies%20like%20Taiwan%2C%20which%20have%20large%20holdings%20in%20US-denominated%20assets%2C%20are%20feeling%20the%20pain%20from%20the%20dollar's%20slide.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20investors%20are%20increasingly%20looking%20to%20hedge%20their%20exposure%20and%20diversify%20away%20from%20US%20investments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPesole%20said%20this%20trend%20is%20part%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bmore%20worrying%20bearish%20narrative%20for%20the%20dollar%26quot%3B%20as%20it%20comes%20at%20a%20time%20when%20Asian%20countries%20are%20negotiating%20trade%20deals%20with%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fus-dollar-index%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Dollar%20Index%2C