o%20five%20years%20%E2%80%94%20as%20though%20it%20hasn't%20yet%20officially%20entered%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBonded%20facilities%20within%20the%20US%20warehousing%20ecosystem%20exist%20as%20a%20duty-deferral%20option%20for%20businesses%20that%20are%20bringing%20goods%20stateside%20but%20don't%20necessarily%20need%20to%20consume%20them%20within%20a%20short%20period%20of%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Flexe's%20head%20of%20network%2C%20Ben%20Dean%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20calmer%20periods%20of%20global%20trade%2C%20this%20looks%20like%20delaying%20the%20official%20arrival%20of%20inventory%20so%20the%20import%20costs%20are%20more%20closely%20timed%20to%20sales%20%E2%80%94%20and%20helps%20keep%20accountants%20happy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20a%20high-tariff%20environment%2C%20the%20value%20of%20deferral%20goes%20up%2C%20so%20immediately%20this%20increased%20demand%2C%26quot%3B%20Dean%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDean%20said%20Flexe%20had%20received%2019%20requests%20for%20bonded%20warehouse%20space%20in%20the%20first%20four%20months%20of%20this%20year%20(largely%20in%20April)%2C%20compared%20with%20two%20for%20the%20same%20period%20in%20each%20of%20the%20prior%20two%20years.%20Another%20four%20requests%20have%20already%20been%20made%20in%20May%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20partner%20Flexe%20works%20with%20in%20the%20Los%20Angeles%20area%20reported%2060%20proposals%20for%20its%20bonded%20space%20as%20of%20April%2029%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20shippers%20who%20are%20in%20a%20position%20that%20they%20don't%20believe%20the%20145%25%20tariff%20will%20hold%20maybe%2030%2C%2060%2C%2090%20days%20later%2C%20so%20by%20holding%20the%20goods%20under%20bond%2C%20there's%20the%20possibility%20that%20they%20might%20pay%20at%20a%20lower%20rate%2C%26quot%3B%20Dean%20said%2C%20but%20he%20cautioned%20against%20that%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMaking%20bets%20about%20where%20tariffs%20will%20be%20any%20point%20beyond%20today%20is%20a%20risky%20business%20to%20be%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20bonded%20warehouses%20ordinarily%20charge%20more%20than%20conventional%20facilities%20anyway%2C%20and%20now%20prices%20are%20going%20up%20sharply.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlexe%20manages%20pricing%20by%20the%20pallet%2C%20which%20earlier%20this%20year%20cost%20%2417.50%20a%20month%20to%20store%20in%20a%20normal%20warehouse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20last%20week%2C%20I%20have%20seen%20bonded%20warehouses%20charging%20%245%20per%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20Dean%20said.%20That%20works%20out%20to%20about%20%24150%20per%20month%2C%20though%20some%20monthly%20contracts%20are%20priced%20closer%20to%20%2452%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEither%20way%2C%20Flexe's%20data%20shows%20that%20bonded%20storage%20is%20now%20three%20to%20nine%20times%20as%20expensive%20as%20what%20might%20be%20considered%20%26quot%3Bnormal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20seeing%20a%20premium%20that's%20beyond%20anything%20I've%20seen%20in%20this%20space%20in%20my%20career%2C%26quot%3B%20Dean%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-trade-war-could-cut-shoppers-products-choice-tariffs-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erising%20costs%20and%20limited%20availability%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20bonded%20warehousing%2C%20Dean%20said%20importers%20were%20likely%20to%20turn%20to%20other%20solutions%2C%20such%20as%20ports%20in%20Mexico%20and%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20retailers%2C%20storing%20inventory%20near%20the%20border%20could%20help%20them%20avoid%20duties%20until%20the%20uncertainty%20around%20consumer%20prices%20and%20demand%20is%20more%20settled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20pay%20the%20145%25%20tariff%20on%20an%20air%20fryer%20from%20China%20if%20they're%20confident%20that%20shoppers%20will%20actually%20buy%20it%20at%20a%20higher%20price%2C%20and%20it's%20beneficial%20to%20have%20pr